Brazil’s Trip to Buy As Many As 40 Airplanes From ATR

-- B y   J o s e   S e r g i o   O s s e
-- 
2011-09-08T14:00:03Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-08/brazil-s-trip-to-buy-as-many-as-40-airplanes-from-atr.html
Trip Linhas Aereas SA,  Brazil ’s
largest regional carrier, said it agreed to buy as many as 40
ATR-72-600 airplanes from ATR Aircraft for $703 million,
according to an e-mailed statement distributed to journalists in
Campinas, Brazil today.  ATR is a joint venture between  Finmeccanica SpA (FNC)  of Italy
and European Aeronautic, Defence & Space Co.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jose Sergio Osse in Sao Paulo at 
 josse1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Francisco Marcelino at 
 mdeoliveira@bloomberg.net  